of india after diwali. holi in india is a festival of fun and frolic and has been associated with the immortal love of krishna and radha. the exuberance and the festivity of the season are remarkable. diwali-"diwali", the festival of lights, illuminates the darkness of the new year's moon, and strengthens our close friendships and knowledge, with a self-realization. diwali is celebrated on a nation-wide scale on amavasya - the 15th day of the dark fortnight of the hindu month of ashwin, (oct/nov) every year. it symbolizes that age-old culture of india which teaches to vanquish ignorance that subdues humanity 